Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.12,0:01:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got all kinds of big people in the world now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.52,0:01:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.88,0:01:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People were smaller when I first got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.72,0:01:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now they're all bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.90,0:01:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you doing, Dr. Robinson?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.47,0:01:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.65,0:01:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we say hi to people here, over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.08,0:01:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.38,0:01:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.84,0:01:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we miss anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.62,0:01:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we miss anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.32,0:01:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The ladies wanted to say hi to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.41,0:01:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sweetheart, yeah, hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.15,0:01:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll come up to this side and go around.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.03,0:01:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we'll go do more things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.35,0:01:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.11,0:01:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.59,0:01:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Sherry, my son's wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.62,0:01:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.88,0:02:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.10,0:02:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.52,0:02:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.30,0:02:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.14,0:02:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.19,0:02:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.07,0:02:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.50,0:02:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we've got to do this side again now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.04,0:02:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is by Lindahl from Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, I remember now, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.76,0:02:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, say I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.97,0:02:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, here's all the people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.55,0:02:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.33,0:02:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.06,0:02:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an honor to be with you again soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.02,0:02:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.88,0:03:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.82,0:03:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody we miss, we don't want to miss anybody, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.32,0:03:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We want everybody to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to miss anybody, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.04,0:03:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Get there and say, where's George?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.09,0:03:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't say hello to everybody, we have to back up the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.31,0:03:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back and pick up George.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.24,0:03:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got 20 more years to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.84,0:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Holy God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We get everybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we get everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We're better.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.03,0:03:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Right on time, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.23,0:03:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Right on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.26,0:03:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's turned on, so I can hear what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:04:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's in the side control room today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.78,0:04:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Gabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.48,0:04:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Gabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.62,0:04:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see how he works.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.94,0:04:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see you do that, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.55,0:04:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the egos dream to be in control.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.73,0:04:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To rule everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.72,0:04:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Make them do what you want them to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Make them think what you want them to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Behave the way you want them to behave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And die for you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.10,0:04:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a minor thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.78,0:04:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You should die for my beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.74,0:05:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's today's rule internationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.62,0:05:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You all should die because of what I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so we start out the lecture with the ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That saves listening to the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.66,0:05:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We start from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.77,0:05:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll talk about leaving anything after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My final piece of advice is the way to the ultimate truth
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is really to become the context instead of the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.04,0:05:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To make one's life a prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.48,0:05:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To become that which people talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.38,0:05:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To be kindly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.76,0:05:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To be forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.06,0:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To see and witness the sacredness of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.24,0:06:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you stay with the context continuously,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.45,0:06:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually what you witness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.03,0:06:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is that everything comes about spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.39,0:06:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,all on its own everything happens automatically is a consequence of the very nature of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.22,0:06:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,itself there is no personal you doing anything all that's happening of its own all you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,do is reject the vanity that there is an eye causing all that to happen the willingness to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,let go seeing yourself as cause all happens spontaneously so with humility you say to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,mind you don't you see what's happening but you don't understand it you don't understand it all
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.84,0:07:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you can provide is an explanation and an explanation is not the reality the explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.18,0:07:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is extraneous to the reality it has to be in order to be an explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.18,0:07:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.78,0:07:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so with sort of a deep humility you begin to witness that everything is happening spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.39,0:07:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of its own because there is potentiality potentiality then manifests as an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and it does so by the power of the field not by the power of you minor little correction
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.77,0:08:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,makes the difference between heaven and hell
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.60,0:08:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,well
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.68,0:08:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,minor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.96,0:08:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd argue meant and all kinds of things all right so don't go with the ego and don't listen to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.36,0:08:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,reason because that's its playground it plays with your head don't let it play with your head
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.15,0:09:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,say I don't want to go there it's a matter of witnessing we said there's two main spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.08,0:09:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,practices meditation and contemplation meditation serves its purposes at specific times in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.59,0:09:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,where you have a mind you're not listening to the narrative right now there are two forms of the self
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't live there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.43,0:09:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because you won't cross the first street
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.63,0:09:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha ha
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.87,0:09:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,together in laden
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.61,0:09:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get taken out by the bus you know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.87,0:09:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,ha
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.40,0:09:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,all right so meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we're just finishing a book nowhere finishing two books simultaneously as we knock off the tail of the last one three
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.44,0:09:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,books
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.58,0:09:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,um
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.74,0:09:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in one of the books anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.96,0:09:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha ha
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.26,0:09:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with meditation and contemplation as a specific subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation has its place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.74,0:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very specific. It's very focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.66,0:10:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It always talks about one-pointedness of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.30,0:10:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But it leads in, to me, meditation can also become a diversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.92,0:10:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Many are the meditators. Few are the enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.90,0:10:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's reasons for it, which we do cover in the lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.65,0:10:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Because meditation is somewhat removed from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.33,0:10:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,For 20 years or something, I did it for an hour in the morning and an hour in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.48,0:10:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if your life gets busy, then you begin to skip it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.70,0:10:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You take a class on meditation, you do a workshop, and boy, you're enthusiastic as all get-out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.53,0:10:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, for maybe four or six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.99,0:10:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then your aunt Tilly gets sick and visits, and well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:10:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you abandon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.70,0:11:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You abandon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.30,0:11:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.82,0:11:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it gets, it becomes held dualistically.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.52,0:11:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a me that's meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,A me here and now that's meditating then and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.62,0:11:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not really you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.66,0:11:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often, I think, there's deviations that are labeled meditation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but they're really methods of achieving altered states of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you stop whatever the thing is you're doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.03,0:11:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the altered state of consciousness disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the states that arise in sort of, to me, artificially-induced states are transitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.80,0:11:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're called satori.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They come and they go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.76,0:11:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can stand up and walk around and open your eyes to the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.56,0:11:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Transitory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.75,0:11:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They are useful in another way because they give you a glimpse that there is another dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.69,0:11:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,another experiential dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.94,0:12:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There is another experiential dimension there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.29,0:12:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the difficulty, as we pointed out in the lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.05,0:12:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll cross over it again today,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is the idea that one can catch the space between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.53,0:12:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any space between two thoughts, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.31,0:12:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody's ever found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.57,0:12:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll clarify that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.05,0:12:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the space prior to the thoughts out of which all thoughts arise, a common field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.85,0:12:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So contemplation then is a lifestyle, a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.54,0:12:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And first, it's a disciplined practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, that's the reality of who you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.43,0:12:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no this and that because you are that to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So that state, that condition that you contemplate,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.39,0:12:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason it works is because it is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.05,0:13:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You imitate your real self artificially.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.87,0:13:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, everything's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.17,0:13:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.81,0:13:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to say everything's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.31,0:13:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's a steam engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.53,0:13:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.37,0:13:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.95,0:13:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm supposed to see its beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.33,0:13:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So you stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.18,0:13:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the horse apples on the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.18,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.17,0:13:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother was Wisconsin, Milwaukee.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.20,0:13:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I grew up, horse and wagons were prevalent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.32,0:13:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And electric cars, gimbals and all, had electric carts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.10,0:13:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked like sort of UPS trucks today, but they're electric.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.74,0:13:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They're quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.24,0:13:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there were the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So the streets would get pretty thick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.05,0:13:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.37,0:13:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The store came by.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.37,0:14:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It came in a wagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.23,0:14:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the fish man, the meat man, the bakery man, the utensils man, the hardware man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything came down the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So you didn't have to really go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.46,0:14:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But on a hot, hot day after a rain, it got pretty strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And my granddad, he said, you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.46,0:14:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.22,0:14:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.28,0:14:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.36,0:14:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.42,0:14:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.46,0:14:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And my grandmother, you know, would call up the sanitation department.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.88,0:14:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And she'd say, it's so strong, it's making the tears come to my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you'd see the guys down there, four breasts, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a different way of life, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.31,0:14:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a different way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, when you're broke, that's a good job sweeping up that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.37,0:14:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have taken it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was too small.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to be stronger, they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.59,0:14:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.79,0:14:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Those big brims are very heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd think they're light.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.79,0:14:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they're pretty heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:14:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,After three hours, they really get heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.59,0:15:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All of that is apropos of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.64,0:15:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is apropos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.24,0:15:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Something has gotten us into a hell of a pickle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.59,0:15:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's best to concentrate on things that are totally unimportant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.21,0:15:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, I was concentrating on something absolutely, totally unimportant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.69,0:15:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Something I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.69,0:15:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, incredible discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.07,0:15:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,See how it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.26,0:15:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'd been thinking about something important, I would have never realized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.13,0:15:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know whether to tell them or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.13,0:15:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.13,0:15:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we tell them what the realization was?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.13,0:15:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.13,0:15:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.13,0:15:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the purpose of this life, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This life was very strange in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.11,0:15:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, starting at age three, I was thinking about life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.32,0:16:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.86,0:16:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was thinking about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.85,0:16:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.85,0:16:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then recurrently at age 12, and periodically, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.24,0:16:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,rather, you know, at least from a historical viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.46,0:16:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,rather unusual in the staggering states.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.02,0:16:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thought was, how come?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.68,0:16:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then one time I was giving a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.74,0:16:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was here someplace, you know, the other hotel, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.30,0:16:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm walking down the aisle, and I could leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know whether I was going to leave or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.52,0:16:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The permission to leave, which has been recurrent also.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.47,0:16:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But no, the body continued to walk on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.77,0:16:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought it looked sort of funny it falling down in the middle of a lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.43,0:16:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's none of my business, so it walked on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.65,0:16:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.43,0:17:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems to be like some kind of a commitment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.39,0:17:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So thinking about nothing at all this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.74,0:17:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with manuscripts of various books around,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems that the purpose is to give witness and to testify
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.31,0:17:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reality of divinity as the source of one's experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.60,0:17:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to testify and give witness to the subjective experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which is of such an incredible nature that it cannot adequately be described.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It emanates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.54,0:17:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It emanates of its own energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.38,0:17:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To give witness to that reality, which is done periodically throughout history,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in various cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.36,0:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it becomes mystified over time and given authoritative,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.56,0:17:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and develops into some kind of a religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.68,0:17:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings me to the crashing halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.45,0:18:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And simultaneously, to develop a scientific objective means of discerning that truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.71,0:18:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, then, the obligation is to witness the inner experience of the revelation of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.61,0:18:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.85,0:18:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you do that, you're going to be able to see the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be able to see the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.01,0:18:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be able to see the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be able to see one's existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.46,0:18:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then to, like, go outside of yourself, the person of that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.78,0:18:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and develop a science of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which we did as the calendar of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And to first be that, witness it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.34,0:18:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because to speak of it with any energy of truth is to spread the energy forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.74,0:18:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.19,0:18:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, because it happened to somebody who also, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.06,0:19:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,was a scientist, physician, psychiatrist, psychoanalyst,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to then go outside the state
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.72,0:19:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and describe it in terminology comprehensible to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.08,0:19:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 400s, in the intellectual, logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.00,0:19:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's one thing to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.88,0:19:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite another to describe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So this gave a yardstick,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.66,0:19:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,an objective means of discerning truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So first to experience the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.93,0:19:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,witness its validity,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.81,0:19:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to testify to it as a reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.51,0:19:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and then to share with the world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.99,0:19:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the means of discerning truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.53,0:19:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which the world has never had to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.90,0:19:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This world has never had any means
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of discerning truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The best that has arisen is the inner state of the mystic,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.94,0:20:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's incomprehensible to probably 99.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.44,0:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of the world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.86,0:20:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not too pragmatically valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.55,0:20:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, you see, first to be it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.68,0:20:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then to describe how it can be described
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.72,0:20:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is verifiable by the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.85,0:20:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and thereby transcend Descartes' duality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.24,0:20:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,of res interna and res externa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.54,0:20:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Take that, Rene.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.04,0:20:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We got them by both, you know what.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.22,0:20:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming and going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.58,0:20:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Res interna.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.66,0:20:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society doesn't understand mystic at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.39,0:20:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm going to try to give it a few sentences
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.73,0:20:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book I'm doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.93,0:21:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystic, that's the inner experience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.11,0:21:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.26,0:21:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Res interna.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.27,0:21:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One's inner subjective state.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.28,0:21:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there is res externa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.07,0:21:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.27,0:21:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.51,0:21:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.69,0:21:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.91,0:21:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.99,0:21:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and what creation actually is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.07,0:21:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's what the mind thinks about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which is totally screwed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.98,0:21:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but useful, thankfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.15,0:21:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you wouldn't be able to get on an airplane
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.75,0:21:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and one end and get off at the other, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.55,0:21:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pragmatically useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.83,0:21:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, having just discovered it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.37,0:21:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd share it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.90,0:21:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Never did in a while I was here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.36,0:21:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but I got it this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.96,0:21:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.26,0:21:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Zappo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.74,0:21:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Look out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.46,0:21:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.52,0:22:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the pointer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.20,0:22:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need the pointer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.76,0:22:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, most of the people here have...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.48,0:22:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.68,0:22:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...have been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.70,0:22:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How many new people do we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.32,0:22:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gracious me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.30,0:22:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here hasn't read Power vs. Force?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.14,0:22:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Get his number.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.40,0:22:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Get his number.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.68,0:22:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.10,0:22:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so a rapid review then.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.62,0:22:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to go over that which we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.60,0:22:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,have shared already,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.57,0:22:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because no matter how many times you go over it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.57,0:22:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you get something new,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.43,0:22:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,just like I did this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.01,0:22:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we want to cover what we have presented before,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.71,0:22:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because from the academic viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.23,0:22:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, as a professor, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.98,0:22:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So from an academic viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.34,0:22:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we do want to make sure that the material is covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.88,0:22:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of the material in and of itself is transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.92,0:22:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to have heard that and go,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.48,0:23:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, wow, you're somewhat different than you were before you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.40,0:23:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.01,0:23:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we want to share it for didactic responsibility to the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.16,0:23:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I respect the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.80,0:23:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it has certainly served mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.66,0:23:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly in the form of science.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.10,0:23:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.96,0:23:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,most of us probably wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.52,0:23:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We would have died early on of typhoid, diphtheria, syphilis,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.48,0:23:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,tuberculosis, polio, all the things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.44,0:23:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When I started out in medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.53,0:23:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was the head of the infectious disease hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.45,0:23:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,people died right and left of all those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.71,0:23:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,typhoid and diphtheria and whooping cough and scarlet fever
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.51,0:23:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and meningitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.01,0:23:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, due to science and logic and reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.36,0:23:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.44,0:24:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's only a fool that belittles the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.72,0:24:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get around to the difficulties of relativistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.75,0:24:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get around to the distorted hermeneutics
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.67,0:24:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of relativism later.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.11,0:24:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.88,0:24:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The beast of relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.86,0:24:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to snatch the innocence of humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.90,0:24:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've declared war on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.75,0:24:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The way I declare war is I put a magnifying glass on it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.15,0:24:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the problem just shoots out at you and you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.10,0:24:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.00,0:24:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we've got this map of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.14,0:24:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.62,0:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because we discovered how to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.02,0:24:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the purpose of this life as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.74,0:24:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mankind never had such a means.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.38,0:25:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was discovered via kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.48,0:25:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that kinesiology was not as presumed a cause and effect
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.23,0:25:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,local phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.09,0:25:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, the response was due to comparing a stimulus
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.99,0:25:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.37,0:25:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And that the fuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.09,0:25:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.94,0:25:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which is like a giant electrostatic field,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.20,0:25:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.57,0:25:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet when a stimulus is provided,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.40,0:25:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it responds in an equal and opposite clarity,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.28,0:25:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,much like an electrostatic,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.02,0:25:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would call the old electrostatic speaker system.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.61,0:25:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens then?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.07,0:25:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In the presence of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.57,0:25:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy goes out through the acupuncture system,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.81,0:25:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the body is strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.86,0:25:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The protoplasm recognizes that which is supportive of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.22,0:26:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is positive and that which is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.88,0:26:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's absent, it goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.02,0:26:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So the test is not true versus false.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.24,0:26:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The test is true versus not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.43,0:26:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.93,0:26:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're an electrostatic fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.43,0:26:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then you only respond to the charge of that which is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.82,0:26:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If a fake truth is presented to you, you don't react,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.94,0:26:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't have any reality to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.72,0:26:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reality, no energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.72,0:26:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't really exist in the realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.72,0:26:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only a proposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.26,0:26:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a proposition, but it's not an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.26,0:26:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're presented with a loving mother
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.26,0:26:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,taking care of her children,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.26,0:26:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,her energy as she makes noodle soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.26,0:26:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a different phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.26,0:26:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes up to 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.52,0:26:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma yoga, the sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.06,0:26:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,one's convenience for the welfare,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.06,0:26:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the survival and happiness of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.40,0:26:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.06,0:27:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's karma yoga.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.06,0:27:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We then ended up with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.25,0:27:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I've been a psychiatrist
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.25,0:27:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and through Columbia Psychoanalytic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.25,0:27:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the so-called emergency emotions down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.25,0:27:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,These are what we've classified as the welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.44,0:27:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been classically aligned this way
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.44,0:27:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as the perennial philosophy for many centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.44,0:27:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You could give us the author of this scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.44,0:27:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,about 10 or 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.44,0:27:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,different authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.44,0:27:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We found it's a very practical,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.44,0:27:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,very practical,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.44,0:27:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with a little expertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.20,0:27:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology only works if you're aligned with knowing the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.30,0:27:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is, in the name of the highest good,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.76,0:27:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you can ask a question,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.76,0:27:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.76,0:27:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ego is subtle
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.76,0:27:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's always trying to proposition some gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.76,0:28:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,some gain, some gain, some gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.99,0:28:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal questions are likely to be often
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.84,0:28:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.89,0:28:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you have to have the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.18,0:28:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be detached, detached,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.18,0:28:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,scientifically, clinically detached.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.18,0:28:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to do it is to ask the question,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.18,0:28:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.18,0:28:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get a book in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.98,0:28:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Susan, I'll do it, I'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.98,0:28:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of the highest good,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.98,0:28:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's well for me to read this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.98,0:28:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.98,0:28:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.98,0:28:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a lot of no's.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.98,0:28:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a lot of yeses, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.46,0:28:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't want to have a position about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.46,0:28:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be impressed by the name of the author.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.46,0:28:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be impressed by the color of the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.46,0:28:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.46,0:28:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.46,0:28:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what does this calibrate at.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.00,0:28:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dedication is through the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.00,0:29:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So anybody can recapitulate the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.00,0:29:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can choose their own numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.00,0:29:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to use these numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.00,0:29:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, clinically,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.00,0:29:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,clinically a lot of people use one to ten you know on a level of one to ten
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.66,0:29:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,how bad is this headache okay we'll go on to the next so transcending these
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.75,0:29:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,levels of consciousness is a manuscript I just finished I just took each level
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.15,0:29:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried to show how to escape because there's two traps on each level one is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.50,0:29:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the gain and the other is the fear of you let go of that gain so that's the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.44,0:29:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,last slide of today if we're still awake we'll get to it we haven't disappeared
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.23,0:29:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,into the these are the enlightened states well the other yeah the other
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.84,0:29:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,scale goes up to 600 because it's extremely rare to go over 600 extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.76,0:30:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,rare one in 10 million something like that and when it happens 50% of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.97,0:30:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the entity leaves the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.91,0:30:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that'd be hard to explain except that is very tempting yeah they say the bliss is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.19,0:30:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and total unto itself and the condition of the body is irrelevant so
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.74,0:30:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,something or someone may come along and look after the body or may not or some
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.84,0:30:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulus may come from someplace but it takes a lot to get it moving again so 50
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.03,0:30:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,percent of the time the people leave you remember from the story of Ruth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.99,0:30:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramana Maharshi, he went into that state as a teenager, I forget how old he was, from
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.19,0:30:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,just an ordinary religious person, he suddenly felt himself dying, so therefore it was an
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.90,0:30:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,actual state.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.89,0:30:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,People talk about going into happy dream states, yeah right, when you feel yourself dying you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.14,0:31:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,know you're about to get there, so he felt himself dying and didn't know if he had or
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.04,0:31:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,not, and he came anyway, he went into enlightened state and didn't speak for two years, he was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.48,0:31:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by himself and when he was discovered he was covered with mosquito, animal bites, insect
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.46,0:31:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,bites and he hadn't eaten, and by entreaty he resumed the physicality, but it was two
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.64,0:31:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,years before he spoke again, and the condition that was experienced in this lifetime was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.89,0:31:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,never spoken about for 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.75,0:31:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It took 30 years to ever even refer to it, and even to refer to it now, it's the state
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.83,0:31:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and you have to stop talking, so we won't talk about it, start talking about that, everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.01,0:32:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,gets their money back, no, no, all right, so 600 is a state of satananda, a state of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.23,0:32:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,bliss, it's self-fulfilling, whether physicality continues after that is frankly totally different
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.49,0:32:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from what it used to be, it's totally irrelevant, it is absolutely irrelevant, so there must
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.17,0:32:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,be some reason for it, and if there is a reason for it, it gets up and walks around again
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.39,0:32:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually resumes life, my god, all those years I never knew until this morning, it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.82,0:32:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,walked around for no reason, for reasons only, you know, you could hypothecate, it wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.70,0:32:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,really until this morning I suddenly realized why I kept walking around, why I didn't fall
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.30,0:32:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,over, right, and the luxury, I mean, I didn't know, I was down that end and I didn't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.32,0:32:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed to walk right on again, I said, well, that's it, you know, all right, so
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.32,0:32:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the state of enlightenment, the state of enlightenment is reached by women and men,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.46,0:33:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,men and women, it is not a sexist proposition, god doesn't have genitals, and the denotation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.99,0:33:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,he is, is only a semantic convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.09,0:33:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity is beyond gender, the non-linear is beyond gender, so, you know, you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.46,0:33:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,politically sexualize religion, which sometimes comes up in the question and answer period
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.12,0:33:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in various parts of the country, you know, I'm a sexist because God's called he, you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.70,0:33:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,have to ask God about it, don't ask me about it, I don't know, it's a quality, it's a presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.83,0:33:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so far beyond gender that it's comical when they come up with a question, all right,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.55,0:33:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so beyond 600 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.39,0:33:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond 600, there is no such thing as a linear reality, and gender, of course, is comical,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.47,0:34:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so here you realize you are, now this is an interesting thing, which we'll get to later,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.85,0:34:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,also a recent discovery, also a recent discovery, below 200 entities, whether they're human
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.32,0:34:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or animal, experience, experience, experience the phenomenon of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.80,0:34:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.80,0:34:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.00,0:34:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.10,0:34:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.16,0:34:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.24,0:34:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.34,0:34:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.36,0:34:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.40,0:34:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.46,0:34:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.48,0:34:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.52,0:34:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.54,0:34:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, there is the experience of experience, experiencing of life, but they don't realize
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.20,0:34:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.94,0:34:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only at 200, you realize you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.98,0:34:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was writing about it this week and somebody got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.14,0:35:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I use this analogy, you say to the kitty, what is it like to be a cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.65,0:35:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat says.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.59,0:35:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean, cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.61,0:35:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're a dumb cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.37,0:35:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.14,0:35:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You are a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.24,0:35:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.66,0:35:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.50,0:35:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I'll get the encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.24,0:35:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the encyclopedia, and I get cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.72,0:35:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we opened it to cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.80,0:35:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat sits there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.74,0:35:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.58,0:35:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I put on my glasses, and I read the whole thing about cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.96,0:35:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, now do you understand what it is to be a cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.19,0:35:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't make any sense out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.81,0:35:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I say, well, the cat, damn it, then who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.02,0:35:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat says, I'm me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.87,0:36:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat realizes that it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.63,0:36:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Overconsciousness level 200 is the awareness of your own existence that you are, that you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.72,0:36:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness of beingness existence is not present below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.48,0:36:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why people below 200 don't care if they kill others,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.38,0:36:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't experience existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.24,0:36:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,so they don't see that they're destroying your capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.42,0:36:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's two different worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.33,0:36:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see it in the evolution of consciousness and its expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.77,0:36:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as the evolution of the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.93,0:36:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that dramatic change at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.95,0:36:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the dinosaur, the rapacious, the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.00,0:36:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.85,0:36:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 in the human domain is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.89,0:37:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The farther down you get, the more serious the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.76,0:37:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at 200, which is the level of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.80,0:37:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual energy begins to flow, and you realize that you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.08,0:37:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the value of human life shoots up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.98,0:37:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People below 200 don't know what it means to exist that I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.19,0:37:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, they have no awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.64,0:37:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.54,0:37:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They are killing that quality if they kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.57,0:37:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Above 200, you have the beginning of morality, ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.77,0:37:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and because the other, now the value of the other becomes important.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.07,0:37:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see that major transition in humankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.61,0:37:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,in behavior, and in the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.99,0:37:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200, the killer suddenly becomes the herbivore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.23,0:38:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200, you see the emergence of the elk, the deer,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.11,0:38:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.33,0:38:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the development of consciousness onward into the 200s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.50,0:38:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And our pets are in the 200s, but the pets are unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.44,0:38:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've never finished the research on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.56,0:38:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a whole project in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.99,0:38:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why an animal in the 200s, as a species, is capable of experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.82,0:38:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and responding to and recognizing love, which is in the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.13,0:38:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So the heart, the heart of the cat
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.41,0:38:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog is capable of responding to the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.51,0:38:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog's wagging tail is 500, and the cat's purr is 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.60,0:38:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute the cat experiences the presence of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.30,0:38:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it starts to purr, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.06,0:38:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Safety, security, and love, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.34,0:38:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does this little animal, as a species, only about 250,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.57,0:39:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize that quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.29,0:39:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.00,0:39:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so that's a whole research thing in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.88,0:39:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we don't want to get stalled out here, but see,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.62,0:39:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,these are the divine states that one can speak
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.91,0:39:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of as the experiential subjective witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.46,0:39:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the energy of that statement is forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.88,0:39:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the collective consciousness of all mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.22,0:39:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to be it and then share it raises the level of the sea, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.24,0:39:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.66,0:39:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But people blow things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.02,0:39:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,People blow things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.70,0:39:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People blow things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.96,0:39:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, that's not a reality, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.87,0:39:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjective reality is not knowable below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.61,0:40:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So for 85% of the people on the planet, this is not a knowable reality, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.90,0:40:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For a considerable percentage of the rest, it's an intellectual belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.48,0:40:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They read that so-and-so said that, that, that, and that, that,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.00,0:40:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore they respect it via the intellect, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.83,0:40:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's 85% of the world we see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.00,0:40:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.32,0:40:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't experience that they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.08,0:40:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. So we realize the importance of within the ego, a structure called the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.68,0:40:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And that experiencer is like a screen in which all these ego phenomena go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.74,0:40:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's one ten-thousandth of a second in advance of the experiencing of subjective reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.00,0:40:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So in meditation, classically, the misinterpretation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.96,0:40:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the subject is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.10,0:41:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the teaching of the Buddha, which I've spoken to him about, as I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.84,0:41:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he agreed, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.26,0:41:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's screwed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.98,0:41:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They figured it, fixed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.83,0:41:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The infinite reality is not between two thoughts, it's prior.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.25,0:41:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the infinite ocean, silent out, non-linear, out of which the linear arises, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.99,0:41:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. As a consequence of the desire to think and the pleasure of thinking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.31,0:41:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.55,0:41:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's the way the world is balanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.81,0:41:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.33,0:41:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's just another way of depicting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.29,0:41:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, isn't this negativity why we have tsunamis and floods and, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.95,0:41:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That's so dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.89,0:41:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it really is dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.04,0:41:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the end times aren't here, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.79,0:42:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,These phenomena went on for millennia before mankind ever got here, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.72,0:42:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And when lightning strikes, saint and sinner alike drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.70,0:42:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Saint and sinner go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.72,0:42:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Saint and sinner get out in the same ship at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.48,0:42:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And all those phenomena went on long before mankind was even thought of.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.22,0:42:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no homo sapien here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.45,0:42:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinosaur kingdom was wiped out, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.31,0:42:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Meteors hit the earth and blackened the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.90,0:42:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And many life forms disappeared, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.84,0:42:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The end of the dinosaur era, hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.00,0:42:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No. So I don't believe in end times and prophecies and a lot, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.18,0:42:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.43,0:42:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.53,0:42:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.71,0:42:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How is life going now?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.17,0:42:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was pretty poor for a long time, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.83,0:42:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Life wasn't too cool at the time of the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.16,0:43:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to have fast-running shoes to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.86,0:43:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then recently, recently, recently, 600,000 years ago is very recent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.78,0:43:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And new evidence, the redating of the fossil, of the skull, is now projected.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.73,0:43:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.81,0:43:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The emergence of homo sapien, even earlier than was previously thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.19,0:43:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.59,0:43:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is only a few seconds ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.81,0:43:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. And now, as you can see from the scale, the scale went like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.43,0:43:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the consciousness level of mankind is rising suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.73,0:43:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.03,0:43:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.07,0:43:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is not going to bring peace, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.73,0:43:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The sword of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.54,0:44:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The sword of truth is somewhat different than peace, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.04,0:44:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,People kill each other over truth, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.54,0:44:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, this rise of consciousness here is going to precipitate very severe conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.07,0:44:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,just by confrontation.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.64,0:44:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is false is threatened by that which is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.86,0:44:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Does not look at it favorably.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.22,0:44:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Decides it better blow it up and kill it before truth gets loose on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.18,0:44:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and brings their days to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.18,0:44:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, didn't Jesus say that I bring you now the sword of peace or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.58,0:44:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.08,0:44:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.94,0:44:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.98,0:44:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Any Christians here?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.96,0:44:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I put their hand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.70,0:44:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Christ say about the sword of truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.96,0:44:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.78,0:44:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.46,0:44:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.99,0:44:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.99,0:44:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The sword of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.54,0:44:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The sword of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.54,0:44:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.90,0:45:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, the sword of truth is not necessarily going to bring you hearts and flowers and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.99,0:45:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,hymns and incense.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.28,0:45:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.70,0:45:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But either you live by the sword of truth or you die by the sword of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.70,0:45:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.70,0:45:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,die by the sword of steel, which is what's happening in today's world. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.90,0:45:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the world conflict now, being threatened by the sword of steel. And what is your
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.55,0:45:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,response? Okay, we go on the next one. So anyway, there we have the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.48,0:45:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal kingdom and the emergence of life over great expanses of time. And it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.05,0:45:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,took like forever for consciousness ever to even get up to 200. As you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.61,0:45:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,these are archeologic ages. We'll move on to the next slide. And here's the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.38,0:45:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom. And here you see these all, these all lived by predation. Therefore, the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.54,0:46:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,ego, as life interacted with material matter, it evolved, you know, as the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.41,0:46:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness rather, the light of God interacted with physicality. Out of it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.51,0:46:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,arose the capacity for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.80,0:46:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Life to survive the way it was, the way it originated. Back here, all these people,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.61,0:46:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,none of them have within themself a source of energy. They're all born without batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.82,0:46:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They need a couple of double A's. You just open the box, there's double A batteries
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.78,0:46:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in the box. But if the batteries run out, they don't have energy. They don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.05,0:46:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.00,0:47:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So how are you going to get energy? You got to get. To survive, you got to get. There
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.69,0:47:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you got the solar plexus fix of the ego for eons of time, and it still operates as the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.63,0:47:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,basis of the animal instincts in the human. All the calibrated levels below 200 are evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.55,0:47:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the persistence of the instinctual drives of the animal, which were necessary for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.57,0:47:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we can't hate ego, because he has to eat. If he was green, we could sit
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.44,0:47:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,him in the sun, and his chlorophyll would re-energize his batteries. But he has no means
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.21,0:48:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to re-energize his batteries. He has to eat. That means he has to eat something, or somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.01,0:48:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat off your thumb, or God knows what it'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.17,0:48:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.47,0:48:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is, you see the nature here. Then at 200, you see the major shift. And we then
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.47,0:48:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,have the animal kingdoms that we love. We love the gorillas. We love the gorillas. I
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.02,0:48:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mean, all normal people love gorillas. They're adorable. And all these animals here, we learn
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.60,0:48:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to love them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.60,0:48:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.60,0:49:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.12,0:49:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Held the baby, then realized the mother would be afraid of her, laid the baby down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.68,0:49:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the gateway for the mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.24,0:49:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was, like, incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.04,0:49:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.90,0:49:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.48,0:49:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We mentioned today Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.45,0:49:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.82,0:49:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is, Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.34,0:49:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He was 470, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.42,0:49:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So people who had a really big impact, intellectually at least, in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.96,0:49:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,were Descartes, Socrates, and Hegel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.27,0:49:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel, we'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.41,0:50:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel defined, you know, he was a major philosopher in the first half of the 18th century in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.55,0:50:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,One of his principles that calibrates extremely high is the principle of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.22,0:50:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, calibrating levels of truth is calibrating like a thermometer.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.64,0:50:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.38,0:50:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the truth of this proposition, entity, or whatever, as compared to the absolute, as compared to the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.72,0:50:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So the recognition of the reality of the absolute as the primary yardstick of truth, then, was Hegel's contribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.57,0:50:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Hegel, at 470, had the intellectual capacity to recognize truth
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.80,0:50:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and give it the respect that was due.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.56,0:51:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then, as we've said before in previous lectures, Karl Marx's, unfortunately, unresolved edible complex
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.86,0:51:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,led him into a hatred of authority and edible problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.36,0:51:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So he disenfranchised the truth of Hegel and substituted a relativistic proposition,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.20,0:51:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the downside of which is the duality of perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.14,0:51:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So all relativism...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.88,0:51:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism, which contaminates today's societies, is due to the duality of dividing things perceptually
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.35,0:51:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,into perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.67,0:51:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Perpetrator and victim depends on point of view, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.93,0:51:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, relativism is, truth is just what you think it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.09,0:51:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You can vote on truth, yeah, because it's only perception denies the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.03,0:51:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.13,0:52:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is brought about all the contention in present society.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.57,0:52:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you calibrate it, if you calibrate it, you find, you know, that it calibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.05,0:52:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely low.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.05,0:52:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you understand the ego dynamics of it, you see that the ego gain, you see the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.49,0:52:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,ego loses, the ego loses when you get up to the mid-400s, because now you've got to go
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.41,0:52:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the world of logic and verifiable reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.97,0:52:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The narcissistic ego loses dominion, and therefore wants to see itself as the arbitrator
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.52,0:52:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality, does not want to surrender its presumptive divinity to something higher than
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.12,0:52:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,itself, not even the level of Hegel, doesn't want to surrender even to 470, much less divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.85,0:52:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or God, much less divinity or God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.27,0:52:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core of the ego, then, is atheistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.27,0:52:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Atheistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.35,0:52:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.35,0:53:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.35,0:53:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if it quotes God, it does so for its own reasons and kills you in the name
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.63,0:53:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.63,0:53:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That way, it gets to still be God and yet pretend not to be pretentious, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.59,0:53:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.59,0:53:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Very clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.59,0:53:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's happened over the centuries, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.33,0:53:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Protestant Catholics are busy killing each other off in 30-year wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.49,0:53:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And the history of the crown of England, of course, is extremely interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.91,0:53:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.45,0:53:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We said to be able to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.87,0:53:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The other problem is rhetoric and deviations from truth occur because people purposely
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.93,0:53:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,ignore stating the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.78,0:53:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A thing is true only within a certain context.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.64,0:53:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In another context, the same statement is false.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.94,0:53:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way of twisting people politically is to ignore the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.12,0:53:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore the context.
