Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.30,0:55:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,things are recorded forever. The field of consciousness, which is a radiance of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.98,0:55:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,energy, which emanates forth as the source of light, the light of God, records
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.50,0:55:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,all phenomena forever, beyond time or location. Therefore, the wonderment of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.51,0:55:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,kinesiology, the kinesiologic test, calibrated levels of consciousness, is you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.07,0:56:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,limited to the linear domain. You can ask anything about anything anywhere in
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.29,0:56:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,time or place.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.79,0:56:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by the Amara.org community
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.97,0:56:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,things that mystify the world, we haven't all saw before breakfast. We track Bin Laden
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.28,0:56:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,every day. Where's Bin Laden today? Well, we put him on the map, he's here, there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.88,0:56:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You track anything and anybody that's going on in the world. And then of course, some of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.10,0:56:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,those things we wrote about in the book, truth versus falsehood, and by the time
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.46,0:56:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the book's published, it's already news, but we knew it long before it was news.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.86,0:56:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, long before it was news. It's useful in things, in the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.67,0:56:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,practical world. You can calibrate the level of intention of a given society, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.98,0:57:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you can calibrate its capability in that area. Therefore, you don't have to walk around being
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.74,0:57:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,blindsided like our country and others have been throughout time. They're always surprised
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.54,0:57:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,by something that is so huge, it's like you're surprised to find an elephant in the living
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.79,0:57:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,room.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.53,0:57:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,500,000 communists north of the Korean War.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.63,0:57:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,500,000 Chinese communist troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.81,0:57:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were surprised by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.20,0:57:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We were surprised by Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.30,0:57:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We were surprised by 9-11.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.07,0:57:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're always like, what are we, walking idiots, imbeciles?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.37,0:57:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised by the bus when it hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.42,0:57:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.20,0:57:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay, we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.64,0:57:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, this is just a verbalization of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.69,0:57:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.71,0:58:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the virtues.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.63,0:58:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We say at 200, the world becomes different.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.23,0:58:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Experientially, the way you experience it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.06,0:58:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience your own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.40,0:58:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience that you are, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.12,0:58:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, other things become more real, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.40,0:58:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are attitudes that begin to become real at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.52,0:58:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, fairness is a stupid question.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.76,0:58:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how stupid fair and honest he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.20,0:58:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.62,0:58:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Americans are blindsided because they're so naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.02,0:58:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They think, see the egotism?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.04,0:58:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody out there must be like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.67,0:58:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not like you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.62,0:58:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't think like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.04,0:58:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't believe like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.32,0:58:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't behave like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.09,0:58:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got nothing in common with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.93,0:59:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,To screw the customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.89,0:59:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,To screw the customer is a point of honor in certain cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.87,0:59:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't, you hang your head in shame
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.19,0:59:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and get beaten when you get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.88,0:59:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no, you're aware of that, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.52,0:59:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And people have been in those cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.78,0:59:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell us, Dr. Kallenbach and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.26,0:59:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, honesty is not even a concept in their,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.36,0:59:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,not even a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.89,0:59:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.71,0:59:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no concern about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.14,0:59:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to get the best price
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.70,0:59:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the best deal you can get,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.68,0:59:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.85,0:59:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody's been to those cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.93,0:59:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He's gotten home with an ancient relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.37,0:59:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,South America is good for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.61,0:59:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a lot of cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.62,0:59:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Genuine relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.58,0:59:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They take you secretly to a hidden place.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.02,0:59:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They got all, this isn't, they got a whole theater
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.28,0:59:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that's worked out and they unveil these things wrapped
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.36,0:59:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in velvet and take it out of a safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.81,1:00:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This, this is from his grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.19,1:00:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was given to him by a brave who had an arrow in his chest.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.19,1:00:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, take this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.35,1:00:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is from my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.61,1:00:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather's hand shook.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.52,1:00:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He put it away because he knew it was so priceless.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.62,1:00:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been kept in the family vault three generations.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.77,1:00:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, the family is poor.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.32,1:00:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The children are sick and need operations.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.37,1:00:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For $10,000, you can have the small one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.67,1:00:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's more of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.43,1:00:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Greed comes up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.25,1:00:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How about 200,000 for all of them?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.98,1:00:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.20,1:00:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't, me with the family, you hear weeping in there, crying.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.44,1:00:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.
