Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.86,1:00:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.96,1:00:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.02,1:00:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.34,1:00:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.42,1:00:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.48,1:00:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So help me God.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.08,1:00:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.78,1:01:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She gives up the family treasure of three generations.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.03,1:01:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Weeping, he comes and tells you, I know you will take good care of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.19,1:01:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll go to the bank with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.35,1:01:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody here is the chap of the world if that happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.12,1:01:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You find it's a plastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.30,1:01:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It was made in China.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.76,1:01:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They make them by the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.90,1:01:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And so would have dishonored him in the eyes of the family.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.08,1:01:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.20,1:01:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a reverse culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.39,1:01:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you understand why America doesn't do too good in international diplomacy?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.71,1:01:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, we'll do the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.46,1:01:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Move to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.62,1:01:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what the mind does.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.82,1:02:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to talk about the mind now.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.94,1:02:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.44,1:02:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This, I want to say I'm going to redo the slide, and I never do.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.68,1:02:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.30,1:02:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the functions of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.02,1:02:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why it is sort of an endless trap, because once you get caught in it, it's pretty
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.48,1:02:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hard to get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.04,1:02:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we doing on time?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.04,1:02:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what's going on in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.42,1:02:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,1115, we take a break?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.34,1:02:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.08,1:02:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know how long it takes to get enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.24,1:02:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it takes 50 years to recover from it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.02,1:02:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say, if you're serious about spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.76,1:02:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that this is not a game, not an intellectual game.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.13,1:03:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you start pulling in the power of divinity by supplication, by declaration, I surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.79,1:03:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,my life to thee, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.68,1:03:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray to be thy servant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.66,1:03:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.66,1:03:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.66,1:03:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You just did something.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.65,1:03:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Life ain't the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.86,1:03:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequences are different.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.92,1:03:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The sequence of options that comes up is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.02,1:03:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You just put a different program on your set.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.02,1:03:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When you do that, always be aware that you may have to make as a consequence some adjustment
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.18,1:03:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,later in life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.18,1:03:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you may.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.49,1:03:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, how do you want things handled?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.91,1:03:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,People think, isn't that presumptuous?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.91,1:04:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not presumptuous, because it's more or less like taking down a glacier, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.64,1:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.36,1:04:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice to people all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.60,1:04:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's like the sun coming down and melting the snow of the glacier.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.36,1:04:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A day, every day, a little of the glacier melts off and trickles down the side of the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.36,1:04:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mountain, and it keeps doing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.44,1:04:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what's holding up the glacier is getting weaker and weaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.50,1:04:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's left of the glacier, the sheer weight of it now, wasn't a problem before, but you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.48,1:04:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can see it's a pending disaster in the eyes of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.24,1:04:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.24,1:04:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying it's my responsibility to teach people what I know, to also be prepared
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.27,1:04:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in case spiritual reality moves much faster than what you would anticipate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.80,1:04:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.33,1:05:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It can just suddenly leave you in a different state.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.63,1:05:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And who's going to pay the bills now and empty the wastebasket?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.85,1:05:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.52,1:05:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.13,1:05:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You pack up your dust.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.13,1:05:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You pack up your duds in the back of your truck and drive away.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.25,1:05:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You throw your tools in the back of the truck, and you drive to the other side of the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.24,1:05:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the end bite.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.33,1:05:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now people will say you've gone crazy, totally mad, and of course you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.52,1:05:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So divine madness can't overtake anyone, and also there's a stage in spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.64,1:05:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,where you get the fire in the belly, where you play with the spirituality, you do courses,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.72,1:06:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you do workshops, and then all of a sudden it becomes like a fever of drivenness, that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.35,1:06:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that is what now has priority over everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.51,1:06:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says to you, even me, yes, even you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.09,1:06:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those decisions come about.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.68,1:06:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's not too uncommon.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.47,1:06:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say in 12 step groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.43,1:06:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not uncommon.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.43,1:06:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not uncommon.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.81,1:06:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those step groups, you know, hey, hey, the relationship worked so long as he was drinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.52,1:06:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She was in charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.52,1:06:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She ran the trick book.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.52,1:06:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She had the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.62,1:06:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the guy is sober, a different person.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.00,1:06:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he's living by different rules on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.12,1:06:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's talking about one day at a time as he does it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.46,1:06:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see how disruptions occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.52,1:06:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's why they have Al-Anon.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.04,1:06:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.00,1:06:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just for the person who's stuck in the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.69,1:07:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't see the trees and still can't see the forest.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.57,1:07:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to give them a sneaky way out.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.55,1:07:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stick with logic, reason, the Newtonian paradigm of causality, and still be spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.51,1:07:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And your sneaky out is quantum mechanics, aha.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.81,1:07:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics now introduces that something other than cause and effect and form is coming
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.75,1:07:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to play, and that's intention, the Heisenberg principle, as we say, everything comes into
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.76,1:07:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,manifestation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.72,1:07:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of intentionality or potentiality, it becoming an actuality when the conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.17,1:07:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,are correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.61,1:07:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle now is an advancement beyond the Newtonian paradigm because it introduces
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.79,1:08:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the enormous power of human consciousness and the will and volition, volition and will.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.66,1:08:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.30,1:08:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.30,1:08:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.30,1:08:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.78,1:08:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.78,1:08:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.16,1:08:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way is that the potential collapses into the particle, which is the actual.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.24,1:08:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I see Henry Stapp has a new book out, which I haven't looked at or read yet, but
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.93,1:08:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.93,1:08:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Henry Stapp, of course, has a website in which he explains this quite neatly, and this is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.79,1:08:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of an adaptation of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.79,1:08:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can still be logical, scientific, rational and not risk being looked at as weird and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.47,1:08:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual and yet see how phenomena that do not fit within the Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.77,1:08:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm can come into manifestation so we'll move to the next yes because now
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.73,1:08:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at somewhat different paradigms of reality the Newtonian is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.13,1:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,predictable the nonlinear is not predictable it's more propositions and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.15,1:09:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihoods so you see likelihoods rather than certainties so it's a
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.53,1:09:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,different dimension it's much more flexible the Newtonian paradigm is a box
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.29,1:09:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,very limited box the minute you open quantum mechanics now you open all kinds
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.81,1:09:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of potentiality and variability so we'll move to the next one this is just to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.52,1:09:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate that the mind thinks dualistically and there's only one
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.66,1:09:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,quality now the calibrated levels of consciousness are just only a means of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.82,1:09:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking the one quality the presence of truth to what degree it's like light or
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.06,1:09:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,dark so there aren't two options
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.20,1:09:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,opposites of true versus false hood there's only relative degrees such as
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.34,1:09:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,heat heat and cold are just manners of speaking they're not separate realities
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.60,1:10:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,heat is present to a variable degree truth is present to a variable degree
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.42,1:10:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,move to the next the progressive fields of realization are interesting and I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.69,1:10:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,writing about them lately because once you identify with the field instead of
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.81,1:10:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.99,1:10:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field, you now put yourself at the likelihood of identifying with the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.08,1:10:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the participant.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.06,1:10:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you focus on the totality of experience from second to second, instead of the annoyances
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.18,1:10:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of the particulars, then what you pick up is the energy of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.30,1:10:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't worry about the particulars because the field is going to see to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.54,1:10:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's either all going to happen if the field is favorable, and it's not going to happen
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.62,1:11:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if the field is not favorable.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.63,1:11:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In contemplation, then, instead of focusing on the specifics of content, you become aware
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.19,1:11:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of the, you might say, the intuitive inference of the totality of the overall field.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.70,1:11:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You become one with the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.39,1:11:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,As you become one with the field, you move out of the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.31,1:11:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.43,1:11:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're now the witness of the movie, the observer-witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.36,1:11:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of seeing yourself as the victim, because to be in the movie, you're always
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.55,1:11:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the victim of the movie, whether you have a good day or a bad day, depends on the vicissitudes
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.49,1:11:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the day.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.49,1:11:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't got any choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.49,1:11:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When you move out of the movie, all is coming about of its own as the manifestation of that
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.39,1:11:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,which it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.35,1:11:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you've moved into the witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.18,1:11:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.53,1:11:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're up above.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.53,1:12:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.53,1:12:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.19,1:12:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you see, you know that because it registers, and you recognize the phenomena
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.61,1:12:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.49,1:12:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's being a participant as you become the field now, awareness, the observer, the witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.68,1:12:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You become the witness of it, and therefore, you don't necessarily have to have any comment
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.13,1:12:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.38,1:12:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.38,1:12:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just got blown up.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.38,1:12:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, followed by a bomb and 30,000 people blown to bits.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.24,1:12:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You go, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.46,1:12:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.46,1:12:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.46,1:12:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.46,1:12:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, so what?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.84,1:12:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been happening since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.10,1:13:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea is to excite you into a positionality so that you cling eagerly to the ego and don't
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.46,1:13:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that you're none of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.86,1:13:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If you aren't a movie, then you're not a movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.02,1:13:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,movie, then of what interest is a movie? Once you realize that you are not a movie. If you think
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.73,1:13:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a movie, then every other movie is fascinating. Once you realize, oh, I'm not a movie?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.27,1:13:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No. What are you? You're the witness of the movie. You're the theater in which the movie is happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.94,1:13:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So to move into the contemplative position then, by supplication to God, you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.48,1:13:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee, O Lord, do I surrender my existence, that I may be thy servant. It's a supplication
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.98,1:14:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,asking not to get, but to be shown. It's more of a yin position. Contemplation is more yin.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.68,1:14:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation tends to be pretty yang, at least in its intention, it's very yang.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.38,1:14:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Very yang. Sit there cross-legged for six hours and don't scratch your nose.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.50,1:14:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll hit you with a stick if you get looked stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.76,1:14:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And fall asleep. That's pretty yang. The inner phenomena, although ostensibly yin,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.52,1:14:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is better realized as a way of being that doesn't get isolated from daily life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.70,1:14:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way you are. You're the supportive watcher, experiencer, and eventually
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.90,1:14:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the realization of reality as awareness itself. That even the watcher and the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.56,1:14:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,are delineation.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.06,1:14:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do the watcher and the witness have any capacity or value? It's because of the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.32,1:15:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of awareness. Then you see, I'm not the subject of the movie. I'm not even the watcher or the
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.79,1:15:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,witness. So you stop trying to delineate it, and you see what you are is a quality,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.99,1:15:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of awareness that is behind the observer-witness, which is the radiance of
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.82,1:15:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity which shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.40,1:15:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which arises all of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.89,1:15:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank thee, we'll take a break. How long?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.25,1:15:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen minute break, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.25,1:15:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,First thing to learn in spiritual work is discipline.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.12,1:16:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The lecture started five minutes ago, and all the crucial things have been said already.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.27,1:16:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very special group of people. But don't think you're special just because you're special.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.78,1:16:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.44,1:16:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what I'm holding in mind is true. What I'm holding in mind is true over 90%, 92%, about 90%.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.02,1:16:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the question was, the only people that are attending a group like this are destined to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.22,1:16:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It says 90%.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.46,1:17:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because the Newtonian paradigm, you think you're being driven by the past. In reality, you're being pulled by the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.11,1:17:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're destined to become enlightened, you're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.59,1:17:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Destiny wasn't to become enlightened, you wouldn't be here, nor would you be picking up the energy of the truth of it to carry forth into the world in subsequent generations, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.34,1:17:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I said to be prepared, because those of you who have already chosen it, consciously or unconsciously, to become enlightened, will then pull yourself into that direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.76,1:17:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And that could bring about changes in your life that can be surprising and quite a bit of a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.95,1:17:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,rising, and quite maximum, quite maximum, maximum, yeah, then you know what maximum,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.27,1:18:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the word means, oh, that's what maximum means, yeah, like wiped out, outside we were just noticing,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.60,1:18:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of causality, the world of the intellect, the world of cause and effect,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.24,1:18:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of the ego, sees life as going from imperfection to perfection, it's imperfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.36,1:18:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so you fix it, it's imperfect, so you paint it, embellish it, you put fur on it, or what,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.17,1:18:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,lipstick, sports shoes, when you become the field, you become aware that what you're witnessing
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.55,1:18:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is perfection moving to perfection, to perfection, to perfection, that perfection is the prevailing
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.73,1:18:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,state at all times, this is not an imperfect rose,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.79,1:18:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming a perfect rose, it's a perfect half rose, it's still a perfect half rose,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.94,1:19:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a perfect developing rose, you understand, so what you witness is perfection, going to
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.85,1:19:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection, to perfection, and what you're witnessing is creation and evolution are one
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.47,1:19:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same thing, all you're witnessing, you're not witnessing causality or change,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.86,1:19:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're witnessing the unfoldment of creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.60,1:19:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because creation and evolution are one and the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.58,1:19:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,creation doesn't go from imperfection to perfection, it's idiotic,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.43,1:19:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be denying the divinity of God, all is perfect, all is perfect, all is perfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.27,1:19:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,all is perfect, evolution goes from perfection to perfection, if you become part of the movie,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.27,1:19:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you think it goes from imperfection,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.17,1:20:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to imperfection, to imperfection, to imperfection, to imperfection, why, because you don't have
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.91,1:20:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole picture, karmically, the best thing you can do right now is get wiped out, why,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.86,1:20:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, you've forgotten all the tens of thousands you slaughtered mercilessly, outside of this
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.44,1:20:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,bodiness, oh, yeah, right, you denied mercy to the innocent, and now you know, you're not
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.19,1:20:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,going to know what it's like, to feel blown up, the world is not in love, so, it is the world,
